==Chapels==
*南侧第三小堂The altarpiece , by [[Pier_Francesco_Mola|Pier Francesco Mola]], depicts St Dominic's Vision.
*北侧第二小堂is [[Francesco_Allegrini|Francesco Allegrini]]'s 1532 ''[[Mystical_marriage|Mystical Marriage]] of [[Catherine_of_Alexandria|St Catherine]]''.
*北侧第三小堂is the 1460 ''Madonna and Child'' by [[Benozzo_Gozzoli|Benozzo Gozzoli]], a pupil of [[Fra_Angelico|Fra Angelico]].

==Depictions in Culture==
The church has been the subject of or appeared in numerous works of art.  [[Antonio_Canaletto|Antonio Canaletto]] made a pen and ink study with grey wash and black chalk, today in the collection of the [[大英博物馆|大英博物馆]], described as depicting "the Church of SS Domenico e Sisto, Rome; with a sweeping double staircase to the entrance, in the foreground a man bowing to two approaching ladies."<ref>http://www.britishmuseum.org/research/search_the_collection_database/search_object_details.aspx?objectid=713994&partid=1 Accessed 6 April 2013</ref>  

In 1906，美国画家[[John_Singer_Sargent|John Singer Sargent]] completed an oil painting of the exterior staircase and balustrade of the church.<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=mXFAr_4aCMEC&pg=PA19#v=onepage&q&f=false ''Twentieth C. Paintings in Asholeum Museum''] by Katharine Eustace, 17-19. The painting now hangs at the [[Ashmolean_Museum|Ashmolean Museum]] at [[牛津大学|牛津大学]].</ref>  Sargent described the ensemble as "a magnificent curved staircase and balustrade, leading to a grand façade that would reduce a millionaire to a worm".<ref>http://www.ashmolean.org/ash/objects/paintings/WA1929.7.php Accessed 24 February 2013</ref>  Sargent used the architectural features from this painting later in a portrait of [[Charles_William_Eliot|Charles William Eliot]], President of [[哈佛大学|哈佛大学]].<ref>http://www.harvardsquarelibrary.org/HVDpresidents/eliot.php Accessed 24 February 2013</ref>  Sargent also made several preliminary pencil sketches of the balustrade and staircase.<ref>Now in the collection of the Harvard University art collection of the [[Fogg_Museum|Fogg Museum]]. http://www.harvardartmuseums.org/art/310499 Accessed 24 February 2013</ref>  

The Church as also been depicted by [[Ettore_Roesler_Franz|Ettore Roesler Franz]] and [[Eero_Saarinen|Eero Saarinen]].<ref>http://www.marks4antiques.com/apa/Eero-Saarinen-Finnish-1910-1961--S-S--32294#sthash.E60JQE3W.dpbs Accessed 7 April 2013</ref>  

